<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--GasolineWash     02-19 0131</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Gasoline Wash,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Burned When Gasoline Explodes in Washing Machine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COOPER CITY, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who poured gasoline into her
washing machine to remove oil from dirty clothes was burned
Thursday when the dryer ignited the fumes, a Fire Department
spokesman said.
   The unidentified woman had added about a gallon of gasoline to
the soap and water, said the spokesman, Russell Brown.
   She was treated at a hospital for second- and third-degree burns
on her arms and face Brown and was released, fire officials said.
   Firefighters found the woman's frightened young son hiding under
a table, said Brown. The child was unhurt.
   The fire quickly extinguished itself and the house sustained
little damage except to the washing machine and windows blown out
by the explosion, said Brown.
</TEXT>
