<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Kiss And Strike,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Room Boy's Kiss Leads to Hotel Strike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 200 employees of the country's
largest hotel went on strike after a room boy was fired for
entering the room of a pretty Japanese guest and kissing her, a
hotel spokeswoman said today.
   The strikers, demanding the room boy be reinstated, had blocked
the entrances of the posh, seaside, 673-room Philippine Plaza Hotel
since Wednesday, said Rosary Ysmael, its public relations director.
   Ysmael said that on Jan. 17, Raymundo Lacanaria, 34, entered the
room of the Japanese woman, embraced and kissed her. The woman
immediately reported the incident.
   Management gave Lacanaria a 15-day suspension after which he was
terminated, Ysmael said. Union officials called the strike after
the hotel refused to take back Lancanaria, who is a union board
member.
   Ysmael said only 200 of the union's 700 members joined the
strike.
</TEXT>
