<HEAD>Girl Killed When Winds Fell Yosemite Trees</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YOSEMITE NATIONAL PARK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wind reaching 60 mph
roared through Yosemite National Park, killing a 9-year-old girl
when a tree fell on a cabin, authorities said.
   Hundreds of campers were evacuated Thursday night and early
today, said park spokeswoman Mallory Smith. She could not be more
specific.
   Jasmine Bitts of Garden Grove was fatally injured Thursday night
when a tree fell on the cabin near the Yosemite Lodge. Her mother,
Nancy Earle, suffered minor injuries.
   The road into the park was closed in early evening.
   The trees included full-grown pine more than 100 feet tall.
   ``We have a wind emergency plan and people were taken to safe
areas, such as the hotel and the main lodge building,'' Smith said.
