<HEAD>Boys Arrested For Making Bombs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MT. LEBANON, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Seven teen-agers have been arrested for
making and exploding pipe bombs for ``kicks,'' police said.
   Two boys were hospitalized with injuries when one bomb exploded
prematurely Jan. 24, Detective John Michalec said Thursday.
   ``We estimate the pipe bombs had the explosive impact of hand
grenades used in Vietnam,'' he said.
   Michalec would not identifiy the boys except to say all are 13
or 14 years old. They were turned over to juvenile authorities on
charges of conspiracy, reckless endangerment and possession of
prohibited weapons.
   The boys exploded at least eight bombs during the last eight
months in fields, playgrounds and back yards, Michalec said.
   The bombs were made from copper tubing purchased from hardware
stores, thousands of kitchen matches and a model rocket fuse or
similar detonator.
