<HEAD>Dormitory Fire Injures Eight Students</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS with 3 grafs to UPDATE with eight students injured, one
in critical condition. Pickup 4th graf pvs, `Many students...'</NOTE>
<DATELINE>MURFREESBORO, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through the lobby of a
two-story college dormitory today, forcing many students to jump 20
feet to safety and injuring at least eight students, authorities
said.
   ``Most had just come from a party, so they were awake,'' when
the fire broke after midnight in Mixon Hall, a men's dormitory at
Chowan College, said police Officer Bryant Cooke.
   One student was listed in critical condition and another in
serious condition at Duke University Medical Center, said Trish
Womble, director of nursing at Roanoke-Chowan Hospital, where six
students were treated for minor burns.
   Many students jumped from second-story fire escapes and windows,
Cooke said. Cooke said one student was found unconscious, overcome
by smoke, on the second floor. Most students had evacuated on their
own by the time firefighters arrived.
   The cause of the fire was still under investigation, but Cooke
said, ``We're thinking arson.''
   The junior college has about 2,500 students.
