<HEAD>Robber Locks 10 In Vault; Flees With Cash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GOLTRY, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An armed robber locked 10 people in a bank
vault and took an undetermined amount of cash from the First State
Bank of Goltry before fleeing, authorities said.
   FBI spokesman Dan Vogel said the robber was being sought today.
The Oklahoma Highway Patrol said he drove away from the bank
Thursday afternoon.
   Among the captives who spent about an hour in the vault were
five bank examiners, employees and customers, said Highway Patrol
Lt. Larry Bennett. No one was injured.
   They were freed when a bank employee called her husband from a
phone hidden in the vault and gave him its combination, said Betty
Johnson, an administrative officer for the state banking department.
   She said the captives tried to call the sheriff's department,
but couldn't get through.
   Vogel said the robber represented himself as a loan applicant
interested in starting a small business. ``He sat down ... and at
that point he pulled his gun out,'' Vogel said.
   Ms. Johnson said the robber ordered people into the vault,
``tossed a briefcase in and told them to fill it.''
