<HEAD>Man Shot At End of High-Speed Chase</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Subs grafs 4-5, `The unidentified ...,' with 2 grafs to give
suspect's identity; Picks up 6th graf, `When the ...' Adds byline.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By SCOTT ROTHSCHILD</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police fatally shot a man early today when he
allegedly cut one officer with a knife and threatened the officer's
partner, following a high-speed chase, police said.
   It was the second fatal shooting by Dallas police within 30
hours and the third this year. Two officers were killed last month
in separate shootings.
   The chase, which began when officers noticed that a car's
license plates were covered with cloth, ended on the Southern
Methodist University campus, the scene a few hours earlier of a
debate among Democratic presidential candidates, police said.
   The man, identified as Thomas Holloway, 34, of Dallas, was
pronounced dead at Parkland Memorial Hospital, said Bill White of
the Dallas County Medical Examiner's office.
   During the chase, police Sgt. R.D. Houston said, the officers
were told that the driver may have committed one or two armed
robberies involving a man with a knife. Houston declined to
identify the officers.
   When the car was stopped, the man got out and cut one officer on
the hand, police said. The officer fired once, striking the man,
police said. The officer's partner then opened fire when the man
allegedly threatened him with the knife.
   At least five shots were fired, police said.
   On Wednesday night, a man who pointed a loaded pistol at an
officer was shot dead by the officer's partner.
   Police Chief Billy Prince ordered two-officer patrols after two
officers were shot to death within nine days last month.
   A transient was killed by police Jan. 23 after he shot and
killed Officer John Chase in a downtown parking lot. In that
incident, officers said some bystanders had urged the transient to
shoot the officer.
   On Jan. 14, off-duty police Cpl. James Joe was killed in a
shootout with two burglary suspects in an apartment complex parking
lot.
</TEXT>
