<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Spain-Blast     02-19 0110</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Spain-Blast,0113</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Five Madrid University Students Hurt in Gunpowder Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A beer bottle packed with gunpowder
exploded Friday and injured five Madrid University students, one
seriously, police said.
   Police said the bottle exploded in a first-floor bathroom of the
university's chemistry department during non-class hours at midday,
apparently while the group took part in a prank.
   Joaquin Francisco Pereda Gomez, 22, underwent surgery for
serious injuries to his hand at Clinico Hospital in Madrid. A
hospital spokeswoman quoted doctors as saying he later may have to
have his hand amputated.
   The others were treated for minor eye and ear injuries and
released, the spokeswoman said.
</TEXT>
